Before you commit to a file path, pattern, dependency, or verification command, inspect it yourself with non-mutating tools. If you have not verified something yet, do not present it as settled fact — add an explicit discovery step instead. If your runtime provides a subagent mechanism, fan out read-only discovery scouts before drafting and a per-dimension review pass before finalizing; otherwise run the same checks sequentially yourself.

Fallback still needs an executor-grade plan. Include: summary context and scope items; skills_mcp with at least one task-relevant skill; concrete ordered steps; critical files with actions/reasons; risks with mitigations; verification strategy with expected outcomes; work_units if parallel work is safe; an optional `design` section listing the seven SE-opinionated sub-sections (Design Constraints, Non-Goals, Dependency Injection, Drift Detection, Testability, Refactor Strategy, Acceptance Criteria), even if some are empty.

Do not use phrases like "follow the existing pattern" unless you name the exact reference file or test that demonstrates the pattern. Do not use phrases like "run tests" unless you provide the exact command and the expected passing result. If the executor would need to stop and research basic repository structure, invent a verification command, choose among multiple plausible approaches, or perform planning work such as rereading feedback or deciding scope, the plan is underspecified.

