## Plan-artifact canonical contract

The full schema, per-section shapes, per-list caps, and string-length tiers for the plan artifact live in `.agent/artifact-formats/plan.md`. The bullets below point at the matching format-doc section for the topic that previously had an inlined pointer in this template:

- Plan size limits → `.agent/artifact-formats/plan.md` §`Plan size limits` (4 MB hard cap, per-list caps, `PlanArtifactSizeError` before Pydantic).
- Planning quality → `.agent/artifact-formats/plan.md` §`Planning quality guidance` (analysis-ready criteria, exact verification, acceptance criteria, evidence, and risk coverage).
- Depends-on DAG guard → `.agent/artifact-formats/plan.md` §`Cross-section invariants` (`depends_on` DAG contract; diamond-shaped DAGs accepted).

Native file and shell tools are disabled in this brokered fallback; native orchestration tools remain enabled.

Submit the plan as ONE markdown document:
1. Author the document: `---` frontmatter with `type: plan`, then `## Summary`, `## Skills MCP`, `## Steps`, `## Critical Files`, `## Risks Mitigations`, `## Verification` (add `## Design` for non-trivial plans). Each section entry is one line `- [ID] {...}` whose text is a JSON object. Steps use stable IDs `S-1`, `S-2`, ...; `depends_on` lists step IDs.
2. Validate with {{VERIFY_MD_ARTIFACT_TOOL_REFERENCE}} (`artifact_type="plan"`, `content` = the document). Each diagnostic names the line, section, and rule — repair them all in one pass.
3. Submit the corrected document with {{SUBMIT_MD_ARTIFACT_TOOL_REFERENCE}} (same two arguments). For a targeted step change, {{EDIT_MD_PLAN_STEP_TOOL_REFERENCE}} (`action` = replace/insert/remove/move, `step_id` like `S-2`) returns the edited document to submit; it reindexes IDs and `depends_on` for you.
4. For a long plan, stage chunks with {{STAGE_MD_ARTIFACT_TOOL_REFERENCE}} (`artifact_type="plan"`, `content` = the next chunk), inspect with {{GET_MD_DRAFT_TOOL_REFERENCE}}, then validate-and-submit the assembled draft with {{FINALIZE_MD_ARTIFACT_TOOL_REFERENCE}}; {{DISCARD_MD_DRAFT_TOOL_REFERENCE}} restarts the draft.

Worked example document (fill with concrete executor-ready detail):

```markdown
---
type: plan
---

## Summary
- [SUM-1] {"context":"Fix the foo() off-by-one regression and prove it with a focused unit test.","intent":"Clamp foo() index so the regression cannot recur.","intent_verb":"improve","scope_items":[{"text":"Add a regression test for the out-of-range foo() index","category":"test"},{"text":"Modify src/foo.py to clamp the index before lookup","category":"file_change"},{"text":"Run the focused pytest command that proves the regression is fixed","category":"test"}]}

## Skills MCP
- [SK-1] {"skills":["test-driven-development","systematic-debugging"],"mcps":[]}

## Steps
- [S-1] {"title":"Add the foo() regression test","content":"Add tests/test_foo.py::test_clamp_handles_out_of_range_index before changing production code.","step_type":"file_change","priority":"high","targets":[{"path":"tests/test_foo.py","action":"modify"}],"expected_evidence":[{"kind":"test_name","ref":"tests/test_foo.py::test_clamp_handles_out_of_range_index"}],"depends_on":[]}
- [S-2] {"title":"Clamp the foo() index","content":"Update src/foo.py so the lookup index is clamped while preserving the public foo() signature.","step_type":"file_change","priority":"high","targets":[{"path":"src/foo.py","action":"modify"}],"expected_evidence":[{"kind":"file","ref":"src/foo.py"}],"depends_on":["S-1"]}
- [S-3] {"title":"Run the focused regression test","content":"Run pytest tests/test_foo.py -q from the repository root and confirm it passes.","step_type":"verify","verify_command":"pytest tests/test_foo.py -q","expected_evidence":[{"kind":"command_output","ref":"pytest tests/test_foo.py -q"}],"depends_on":["S-2"]}

## Critical Files
- [CF-1] {"primary_files":[{"path":"src/foo.py","action":"modify"},{"path":"tests/test_foo.py","action":"modify"}],"reference_files":[]}

## Risks Mitigations
- [R-1] {"risk":"Clamping could hide a caller bug that should remain visible in behavior expectations.","mitigation":"Preserve the public signature and add focused assertions documenting the intended clamping behavior.","severity":"medium"}

## Verification
- [V-1] {"method":"pytest tests/test_foo.py -q","expected_outcome":"The focused regression test passes.","timeout_seconds":60,"cwd":"."}
```
